      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i need some help with these two interview transcripts for a customer service position. i need u to summarize how well each person communicates their ideas and if u think they'd be a good fit for a professional, client-facing role. here they are:\n\nCandidate A:\nInterviewer: Can you tell me about a time you handled a difficult customer?\nCandidate A: Certainly. In my previous role, I encountered a client who was quite frustrated regarding a shipping delay. I listened to their concerns patiently, acknowledged the inconvenience, and then provided them with a clear timeline for the resolution. I found that staying calm helped de-escalate the situation effectively.\n\nCandidate B:\nInterviewer: Can you tell me about a time you handled a difficult customer?\nCandidate B: Yeah, for sure. Back when i worked at my last job, i had this customer who was real frustrated 'cause her package was running late. I just sat there and listened to what she had to say, let her know i understood why she was upset, and then i told her exactly when it was gonna get there. Keeping it chill like that really helped the situation calm down.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
